Description: OfferJar is a simple, automated plug-in that allows buyers and sellers to bargain in real time to capture close more deals.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: OfferJar allows buyers to purchase items in real time for the price they are willing to pay. They are able negotiate and close their own deal.  No need to wait for sales, coupons or discounts.  Approved by eBay as compatible.  Buyers and Sellers are prevented from closing large number of transactions because they are not able to negotiate with each other in real time.  When a seller offers a product above what the buyer is willing to pay a sale is lost, when the price is too low a margin is lost. A tool is needed that will allow buyer and seller to negotiate and achieve an equitable price. OfferJar provides that tool.   There is no other application available which provides this service.   OfferJar is an innovative and new automated negotiations platform. By using a proprietary 2-way bidding algorithm, OfferJar aims to bring online retail to a new level of collaborative deal-making. Current online retailers suffer from gaps in product pricing and buyer willingness to pay. There is a lack of information that allows sellers to appropriately determine the best price to offer each individual consumer, as such, many sales are left on the table. Under all available applications there is a delay of hours, sometimes days to get a response to buyers’ offers. Because of that, very often the buyer completes the transaction at another venue.  If it doesn’t work fast you into the next thing.   OfferJar allows sellers to upload any and all unsold items and uses a seller directed toughness scale to offer negotiated discounts to buyers.  This allows the seller, at no cost in labor once it is set on auto-pilot, to achieve a sale that would otherwise not have occurred, and turn inventory over faster.   For more details see links to Investor Deck and Product Offering.

Description: Tico is your Intelligent Agent to monitor, evaluate, and consolidate your credit card transactions in one place (Credit Card Detective).
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Tico is your Intelligent Agent to monitor your credit card transactions. No more concerns about credit card fraud. All your transactions in one place to stay on top of everything.     Tico’s technology is based on learning your spending patterns and notifying you about anomalies. With three simple steps, you can add your credit cards, educate Tico about your spending patterns, and contact your bank in case of any disputes. Each transaction is categorized as either blue, yellow, or red. Red indicates suspicious transaction that requires your immediate action; yellow means there’s a warning regarding the transaction, and blue indicates the transaction is normal. If a transaction is marked as suspicious, Tico will tell you why it is suspicious. You can further educate Tico by verifying (swiping right) or reporting unfamiliar transactions (swiping left).   Tico has also made it very easy for you to search and review your transactions and navigate through historical purchases.

Description: MinnDak believes communication builds trust and is critical to the client relationship.
Full Description: Chris Buckingham began his career in Information Technology in 1998, traveling throughout rural Alaska providing services for a communication and internet service provider there. Eight years later, he answered the call to return to the Red River Valley, where he worked until founding MinnDak Computer Services of Fargo, ND, in May 2009. Chris currently resides in Rothsay, MN with his wife, Terri, and daughters, where he serves as Mayor and a standing board member of the Rothsay Economic Development Authority. Over his years working as an IT technician providing standard break-fix services, Chris became increasingly dismayed as he watched companies spiral into chaos when problems with their servers, desktops or other devices cropped up. Because these businesses had no indication that problems were looming and couldn’t have addressed the issues if they had, they suffered serious production losses and encountered severe customer dissatisfaction that often put their businesses at great financial risk. Deciding there had to be a better way to do business, Chris focused his company’s efforts on providing Managed Services in order to help businesses reach their full potential by providing ongoing services such as remote monitoring, maintenance and prevention that save them thousands of dollars in emergency service fees and downtime. A well maintained, proactively serviced computer system always runs better than the alternative.

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Migralex is different from most other headache medications. First of all, it has no caffeine. Caffeine is an active ingredient in a variety of over-the-counter and prescription headache drugs. Caffeine does enhance the pain-relieving properties of other medications. However, caffeine is also responsible for causing or worsening headaches in millions of people. Almost everyone who drinks more than one or two cups of coffee a day knows that skipping their usual cup of strong morning coffee can result in a severe headache. The existence of caffeine withdrawal headaches is also well documented in scientific studies. Caffeine also causes or worsens anxiety, depression, insomnia, acid reflux, palpitations, and other problems.
